Package io.jstach.rainbowgum

Interface KeyValues

All Known Subinterfaces:
KeyValues.MutableKeyValues
public sealed interface KeyValues permits KeyValues.MutableKeyValues (not exhaustive)
Key Value Pairs similar to a Map<String,String> but optimized for memory and less garbage (no iterators).

The integer index used in the low level access are not in array order and thus start() and next(int) should be used to iterate over the key values instead of manually incrementing.

The observed order of the current default Key Value Pairs is insertion based ordering but that should not be relied on as other implementations may change that.
